<DOC><DOCNO> AP901205-0097 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-12-05-90 1319EST</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-Israel-Unrest     12-05 0185</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Israel-Unrest,0195</SECOND><HEAD>Gunfire on an Israeli Bus in the West Bank, Three Wounded</HEAD><BYLINE>By ALLYN FISHER</BYLINE><BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Gunshots were fired at an Israeli bus in theoccupied West Bank today and at least three people were wounded,the army and Israeli reports said.   Military sources said several shots were fired at a bus ofEgged, the national bus company, as it drove on a main thoroughfarenear the Jelazoun refugee camp, north of Ramallah in the West Bank.   Three civilians were slightly wounded and rushed to HadassahHospital in Jerusalem, the sources said. They gave no furtherdetails.   The shooting occurred about 6:30 p.m., when most Jewish settlersin the West Bank return from work in Israel, the national Itim newsagency reported.   Israeli soldiers began searches in the area, the report saidwithout elaborating.   The shooting came after newspapers, quoting army officials,reported that Palestinians were likely to turn to firearms as theirrevolt against Israeli rule of the occupied lands neared its thirdanniversary.   Leaflets distributed by uprising leaders earlier this week urgedPalestinians to attack Israelis ``using any means.''</TEXT></DOC>